title: Mar-a-Lago members mad Trump shut down club for weekend
text: show ad EXCLUSIVE: 'We can't even go to the bar!' Members of Mar-a-Lago are outraged that President Trump is closing the doors to the Palm Beach club for the weekend - after shelling out up to $200,000 to join and $15,000 in dues Intelligence experts criticized President Trump for preparing his response to the firing of a test missile by North Korean while dining among members last week 'We are pi**ed off to no end,' said one Mar-a-Lago member, who asked that his name not be used for fear of being shunned by Trump if he talks to the press Another member said Mar-a-Lago's reservations clerk told him the Secret Service is no longer allowing members in while Trump is at the club A charity gala planned months ago to benefit the Dana-Farber Cancer Institute will be allowed to go on Saturday night But gala goers who paid $1,250 each to attend will not be allowed to mingle in the entire club like those who attended previous events were allowed to do Published: 22:12 GMT, 17 February 2017 | Updated: 04:36 GMT, 18 February 2017 147 shares
